<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="67" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,567,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1108,1134]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Don" authorityYear="1823" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[371,534,1108,1134]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[371,534,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Clidemia hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed species from Central America to 
<collectingCountry box="[1140,1251,1108,1134]" name="Argentina" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="67" pagination="591 - 646" refId="ref22935" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Souza, M. L. D. R., Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A. (2006) Melastomataceae na Reserva Biologica de Poco das Antas, Silva Jardim, Rio de Janeiro, Brasil: aspectos floristicos e taxonomicos. Rodriguesia 57 (3): 591 - 646." type="journal article" year="2006">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis box="[1396,1452,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[245,313,1144,1170]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it is found in almost all states, usually in open areas, sunny and very anthropized habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="67" pagination="591 - 646" refId="ref22935" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Souza, M. L. D. R., Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A. (2006) Melastomataceae na Reserva Biologica de Poco das Antas, Silva Jardim, Rio de Janeiro, Brasil: aspectos floristicos e taxonomicos. Rodriguesia 57 (3): 591 - 646." type="journal article" year="2006">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis box="[136,196,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Reginato, M." box="[281,645,1180,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref26186" refString="Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Reginato, M. (2012) Clidemia. In: Baumgratz, J. F. A., Bernardo, K. F. R., Chiavegatto, B., Goldenberg, R., Guimaraes, P. J. F., Kriebel, R., Martins, A. B., Michelangeli, F. A., Reginato, M., Romero, R., Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Woodgyer, E. (Eds.) Melastomataceae: Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / (accessed July 2012)." type="url" year="2012">Michelangeli &amp; Reginato 2012</bibRefCitation>
). It is classified as Vulnerable for the municipality of 
<collectingRegion box="[1282,1451,1180,1206]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[144,337,1216,1242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" pagination="30 - 31" refId="ref22589" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (2000) Melastomataceae. In: Di Maio, F. R. &amp; Silva, M. B. R. (Eds.) Especies ameacadas de extincao no municipio do Rio de Janeiro: flora e fauna. Secretaria Municipal de Meio Ambiente, Prefeitura da Cidade do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, pp. 30 - 31." type="book chapter" year="2000">Baumgratz 2000</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[386,491,1216,1242]" name="Malaysia" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, Hawaii, 
<collectingCountry box="[598,702,1216,1242]" name="Tanzania" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[760,895,1216,1242]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
it has become a naturalized weed (
