</taxonomicName>
only occurs in Dense Submontane Ombrophilous Forest. It is distinguished mainly by the inner torus with an irregular tooth-fimbriated membranaceous ring, and calyx with slightly denticulate internal lobes or reduced to a membranaceous and sinuous ring. Additional illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A." box="[304,574,1396,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" pagination="591 - 646" refId="ref22935" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Souza, M. L. D. R., Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A. (2006) Melastomataceae na Reserva Biologica de Poco das Antas, Silva Jardim, Rio de Janeiro, Brasil: aspectos floristicos e taxonomicos. Rodriguesia 57 (3): 591 - 646." type="journal article" year="2006">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis box="[434,490,1396,1422]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Matsumoto, K. &amp; Martins, A. B." box="[633,968,1396,1423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" pagination="19 - 22" refId="ref25752" refString="Matsumoto, K. A &amp; Martins, A. B. (2009) Clidemia. In: Wanderley, M. G. L., Shepherd, G. J., Melhem, T. S., Giulietti, A. M. &amp; Martins, S. E. (Eds.) Flora Fanerogamica do Estado de Sao Paulo, v. 6. Instituto de Botanica, FAPESP, Sao Paulo, pp. 19 - 22." type="book chapter" year="2009">Matsumoto &amp; Martins (2009)</bibRefCitation>
.
